The paper deals with the construction of spanners for doubling metrics, which is a topic in computational geometry and graph theory. The use of net trees and cross edges suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The mention of hop-diameter and lightness suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the mention of fault tolerance suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
